1. grep
    https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/howto-use-grep-command-in-linux-unix/
    grep word file1 file2
      search line containing word in files
    grep -w word file1 file2
      search whole word matching in files
    grep -v word file1 file2
      reverse match
2. Use the egrep command as follows:
    $ egrep -w 'word1|word2' /path/to/file
    dmesg | egrep '(s|h)d[a-z]'
      match all sd[a-z] or hd[a-z]
    http://www.computerhope.com/unix/uegrep.htm
    
